## 5. ENVIRONMENT & DEPLOY RULES

| Environment | How to deploy | Who can approve |
|-------------|--------------|-----------------|
| Local dev | `pnpm dev` | Anyone |
| Preview | Firebase preview channel | AG, GA, CC |
| Production (`main` branch) | CI/CD auto-deploys on merge | Chase only |

**Never push directly to `main`.** Always use a feature branch. CI runs typecheck + lint + build — do not skip.

---

## 6. CODE QUALITY GATES

Before marking any task complete:
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes (no TypeScript errors)
- [ ] `pnpm lint` passes
- [ ] `pnpm build` succeeds (no build-time errors)
- [ ] No `export const` named exports from `page.tsx` files (Next.js 15 rejects them)
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or API keys
- [ ] No `console.log` left in API routes (use structured logging)

---

## 7. PATTERNS TO ALWAYS USE

**Auth check in API routes:**
```ts
const session = await auth();
if (!session?.user) return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
```

**Prisma error handling:**
```ts
try {
  const result = await prisma.model.findMany({ ... });
} catch (e) {
  console.error('[route] DB error', e);
  return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Internal error' }, { status: 500 });
}
```

**Stripe — always use the lazy singleton:**
```ts
import { getStripeClient } from '@/lib/stripe';
const stripe = getStripeClient();
```

---

## 8. PATTERNS TO NEVER USE

- `new Stripe(key || '', ...)` at module level — throws in CI when STRIPE_SECRET_KEY is absent
- `export const API_ROUTES = ...` from page.tsx files — Next.js 15 rejects non-reserved named exports
- `prisma.$queryRaw` without parameterized inputs — SQL injection risk
- `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without `isomorphic-dompurify` sanitization
- Hardcoded email addresses in code (use env vars or constants file)

---

## 9. THE HDX THESIS (Read Before Any Copy or UI Work)

We do not build foundation models. We build the rails.

- **Plumbing over Pixie Dust:** AI is a deterministic tool in a workflow. "Vertex AI classifies the scan, then Cloud Function updates the CRM." Never "AI magic."
- **Unit Economics Obsession:** $74/mo HDX node vs. $8,500/mo IT department. Every feature should reduce headcount cost, not add complexity.
- **Sovereign Architecture:** Six entities, strict data boundaries. Delta Dawn reads across all — read-only only.
- **Closing line (required on all brand pages):** "We build local. The value stays local. We grow from within."

Tone: Unromantic. Pragmatic. CTO-to-operator. No hype words.

